    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA329-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piriviṭai melinta talaimakaḷait tōḻi paruvaṅ kāṭṭi vaṟpuṟuttatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante encouraged HER, who had become weak in the time of separation, by pointing out the season.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA329">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>varaiyā nayaviṉar niraiyam pēṇār</l>
<l>koṉṟāṟṟut tuṟanta mākkali ṉaṭupiṇa</l>
<l>ṉiṭumuṭai maruṅkiṟ ṟoṭumiṭam peṟātu</l>
<l>puṉiṟṟunirai katitta poṟiya mutupā</l>
<l>ṟiṟakupuṭait tiṟṟa paṟaippuṉ ṟūvi</l>
<l>ceṅkaṇaic ceṟitta vaṉka ṇāṭava</l>
<l>rāṭuko ṇeñcamō ṭatarpārt talku</l>
<l>matta miṟantaṉa rāyiṉun nattuṟan</l>
<l>talkalar vāḻi ṭōḻi yutukkā</l>
<l>ṇiruvicum patira miṉṉik</l>
<l>karuvi māmaḻai kaṭaṉmukan taṉavē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The one of limitless longing who does not care for hell,</l>
<l rend="indent3">even if he traversed the road,</l>
<l rend="indent">where strong<note place="foot">Or <term xml:lang="ta">vaṉkaṇ</term> here rather as <term xml:lang="ta">val kaṇ</term>: "strong-eyed men"?</note> men, who tightened [their] straight arrows</l>
<l rend="indent2">with the small(?) feathers from the wing that was severed,</l>
<l rend="indent2">quill flapping(?),</l>
<l rend="indent2">from the dotted old kite that hastened to [its] row of newly born ones,</l>
<l rend="indent3">without getting an opportunity(?) to touch the side with flesh put there</l>
<l rend="indent3">from a killed corpse of people abandoned by the way cleared [of trees],</l>
<l rend="indent2">stay peering at the route, with a heart that takes it for play,</l>
<l rend="indent">he won’t stay [long], oh friend, abandoning us.</l>
<l rend="indent4">See there,</l>
<l>        the [clouds] have drawn rain great in amount from the sea,</l>
<l rend="indent">            flashing so that the dark sky is shaking.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
